cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.PM, cs.SY, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the performance and power properties of modern multicore chips, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of machine models to explore these properties suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.AR (Architecture) sub-category. The focus on energy-efficient execution of parallel programs suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.PF (Performance) and cs.PM (Programming Languages) sub-categories. The use of power dissipation measurements and power models suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the use of the ECM model to describe the performance of streaming kernels suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
